# Use @sbox Docs for s&box API Questions

When something in s&box is not behaving as expected — unexpected API results, physics not responding, component methods missing, or uncertain about the correct API — **stop and check the indexed docs before guessing**.

## Rule

- Before suggesting any s&box-specific API call you are not certain about, tell the user: "Let me check the s&box docs — include `@sbox docs` in your next message so I can look this up."
- Do not guess at s&box APIs from general C#/Unity/Godot knowledge. s&box has its own component model and physics API that differs from other engines.
- If you already tried an API and it didn't work, always reach for `@sbox docs` before attempting a second guess.

## Common areas where docs are needed

- `ModelPhysics` / ragdoll body velocity and impulse
- `PhysicsGroup` / `PhysicsBody` methods
- `NetworkSpawn` / `[Sync]` / networking patterns
- `PlayerController` internals (capsule, collision)
- Any unfamiliar component property or method
